      "code": "sa",
      "role": "adstrate",
      "weight": 0.2,
      "notes": "Very heavy Sanskrit adstrate: ~50% of formal vocabulary"
    }
  ],
  "notes": "Standard Malayalam (Kerala). Descended from Old Tamil, diverged c. 9th–13th century CE. Unique phoneme: ⟨ഴ⟩ = /z/ (derived from Proto-Dravidian *ḻ, retained as /z/ only in Malayalam). Uses the most complex Brahmic script (~60 base characters). Phonemic gemination. Heavy Sanskrit vocabulary in formal register.",
  "quality": "research",
  "script_type": "abugida",
  "inherent_vowel": "a",
